comments: A little unclear on the expert opinion rating question in the context of the survey

There are some exceptions to be made for champs such as Ornn who don’t need to back as regularly or champs with lifesteal and no mana such as Morde, who might have a weaker laning potential but should still come out on top of cs.

Some of these matchups are really jungle dependent. Thinking laning Phase is about 1v1 ing your opponent is just wrong. It’s all about waves, priority and playing around your jungler. Looking at these matchups isolated is possible but kinda pointless, for example Camille-Jax matchup or irelia-Darius. How far one of them gets ahead really depends on whose Jungler is around and how cocky can you play.

I would imagine a diamond player wouldn't have biases or lie about how much they see lane matchups win. I would think their experience would dictate that and I would be inclined to believe them most times
More expansion towards other lanes and/or types of players.

I did not like the phrasing of which champion will have more gold after laning phase. Gold is not the only important thing, especially in top lane. "Who would win this lane?", would be a much better question, when you think of builds like Gangplank with old Kleptomancy. The definiton of winning a lane could be: be able to destory the tower first, be able to roam without losing much, be able to play with your jungle to get objectifs on the map without losing much.
These graduations depends on the meta.
Any ranged vs melee assassin matchup is highly dependent upon roam frequency/success rate for overall gold income.
Top Lane used to be the lane I played all the time, but in the past year, I've moved to mostly playing Mid Lane and only sometimes playing Top Lane. This may have influenced my answers a bit.

Maybe I'm just washed because I haven't played the game at a high level in four~ years, but I imagine a number of the champs like Talon/Kat/Qi all love to just permaroam, even during laning. Often I wasn't sure how to rate matchups because in the pure 1v1 one laner can destroy the other, but jungle matchup and roaming conditions can trivialize the actual 1v1. Not sure what the purpose of the study is, but I think distinguishing between pure 1v1 laning vs jungler influence and roaming would give more less subjectivity to how people answer.

Might want to include an option for "unranked" rather than just below 30 and then iron/bronze/silver/ etc. I personally haven't played competitive since season 3 so unranked is usually what I describe myself as.
Honestly I suck at midlane and have no clue how any of these matchups go, but i used my knowledge of these champs abilites to try and figure it out.
This was a bitch to fill out on mobile so i just put as Close to 50 as i could on THE last Collection of sliders. And i dident get te he last queation.

At the diamond level, I don’t completely expect the lane to just be Champion A vs. Champion B. I would expect the jungler to assist, and I believe that would impact the lane no matter how much of a counter one champion is to the other.
